title: For Sale:  Winchester 1890 Deluxe 22LR Case Colored Stunning!
postcontent: NO RESERVE! More photos soon. Watch for more high-end firearms I'll be listing for auction in coming weeks - Colts, Winchesters and more! Here's one for the Winchester collectors - very popular these days, very collectible and who knows what the future holds. Got money in the stock market? Time to bail and invest in something that you can hold in your hand. Here's a Winchester 1890 Deluxe, in a beautiful case-colored finish! I have obtained some very interesting info on this one. Restored 27 years ago by Guns Unlimited - "World's Finest Custom Gun Work" - which was owned by none other than Thomas Haas of the Ponderosa Ranch in Spencer Indiana! The name may ring a bell as his work is pictured in The Book of Colt Engraving. Haas and Horacio Acevedo are famous for the exact copy of the "Sultan of Turkey" Colt Dragoon. The original Sultan was given to "His Highness the Sultan of Turkey" by none other than Sam Colt! The Dragoons are pictured in the colt book side by side and they are a beautiful pair. The original resides in the Metropolitan Museum the copy was featured in the collection of Buddy Hackett. Hass was famous for the custom Patersons he built, along with 25 or so Colt Walkers and the many Colt Single Actions he converted to 22lr. When Colt was unable to finish 1,000 Texas Ranger Commemoratives for the 150th celebration of the Texas Rangers, Haas completed them, and probably saved Colt from an expensive lawsuit. As an advisor on many western movie sets, he became friends with several Hollywood types, including Elvis, Lash LaRue, Dale Robertson, and Mel Torme. He was also a technical advisor to Gary Cooper, Burt Lancaster, Vera Cruz, Victor Mature, and many others. This particular rifle was at his shop for over four years and an apologetic letter from the shop verifies this. Sadly, he passed away 13 years ago. Truly a rare piece with a colorful story behind it and worthy of any collection! Features a gorgeous high grade walnut pistol grip stock with fantastic figure and excellent checkering. Beautifully colored crescent butt plate, along with the lower tang and hammer. The pistol grip cap is mounted with an engraved screw. The case-colored receiver is excellent, tastefully done, not the bold phony colors sometimes seen. The 24" barrel appears to be lined and has the Winchester patent dates and address as shown. The front sight is an ivory bead when down and a globe sight when raised. The barrel has a two leaf sight and the rear tang sports a Lyman marked sight. The sights alone were very pricey. I'm sure you know that original deluxe 1890 rifles can run upwards of five figures and are very seldom seen for sale.
